label: Planet Mu Records Ltd.
description:
Footwork OG, DJ Manny helps define the style in its late teenage years with a strikingly minimal, sensual, spaced-out batch of R&B and drill-tinged aces

Aye, we want some of whatever DJ Manny was smoking while he made the ‘Control’ EP. On all five cuts he sounds stoned as heck and deep in his thing, rolling out from the louche, string-slashed swerve of ‘Control’ to the exquisite, drill-tipped, sub-cushioned music box melody of ‘Spaceship’, and FM synth chord flair of ‘Time Travel’ via... more

title_full:
Michael J.Blood x Rat Heart

              —
              Nite Mode Vol. 2
            
              (BodyTronixxx)
label: BodyTronixxx
description:
Punk soul boys Michael J.Blood and Rat Heart stoke up the SP-404 and the mic for a follow-up to 2022’s sought-after first Nite Mode volume, doubling down on its brand of smashed R&B romance in a way that feels primed for long summer nights.

The MVPs don their silk smoking jackets, trackies and slippers for a properly greazy, hour-long suite of smudged and screwed beatdown laced with aching original vocals and oodles of slanted soul. Going on like Rezzett with a thang for the afters, they’re... more

Razor-cut UK rave recombinations by the don Semtek, imagining Steve Gurley vs El-B on a dank UKG flex, beside a proper bassbin botheration
